The paper deals with the problem of clustered planarity, which is a topic in graph theory and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves graph theory concepts such as connectivity and subgraphs, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problem, which relates to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
